co.cask.cdap.api.dataset.module
Interface DatasetDefinitionRegistry

@Beta
public interface DatasetDefinitionRegistry

Registry of dataset definitions and other components in a Datasets System. The implementation of this interface doesn't have to be thread-safe.

Method Detail

add

void add(DatasetDefinition def)
Adds DatasetDefinition to the registry. After it was added it is available thru get(String) method.

Parameters:
def - definition to add
Throws:
IllegalArgumentException - if registry already contains dataset type of the same name as given definition

get

<T extends DatasetDefinition> T get(String datasetTypeName)
Gets DatasetDefinition previously added to the registry.

Type Parameters:

Parameters:
datasetTypeName - dataset type name, should be same as DatasetDefinition.getName()
Returns:
instance of DatasetDefinition
Throws:
IllegalArgumentException - if registry does not contain dataset type of a given name

hasType

Parameters:

Returns:
